29 and 
9-bromo-1-(4-chloro-phenyl)-3-(4-tolyl)-8H-pyrido[2',3':4,5]pyrimido[6,1-b]quinazolin-8-one 
36 exhibited even more potent anti-inflammatory activity and low gastric 
ulceration incidence compare to reference standard Indomethacin. Since compound 
23, 24, 29 and 36 exhibits both anti-inflammatory activity and PDE1 inhibition, 
it needs further detailed studies.

